As the author of that table, I'd like to nip this in the bud: The test is anti-Buddhist. I am not anti-Buddhist and neither is Zyn. It was written to be intentionally provoking, sure, but only to the extent of wanting to throw a reader a curveball if they were becoming complacent about understanding the motivations behind the test, not as any sort of propaganda. As WrongJohnSilver noted, it's not the only  condition but it is certainly supposed to be the most unexpected one.

Now, as for why the test dislikes Buddhists so much, I'm going to pull the college-textbook-handwave and say  humanity by propagating the species might view Buddhist ideas as a threat.

Or maybe it just hates Buddhists.







